  "text": "Lobulation is an important category of CT imaging signs, which is dependent on the ingrowth of connective tissue septa containing fibroblasts derived from perithymic mesenchyme [CITATION_1] . It is normally related with malignant lesion, though it also occurs in up to 25% of benign nodules [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Visually, a lobulation shows the indentation which appears at the edge of round or oval lesion. Figure 1 shows an example of lobulation, where the small rectangle indicates the region annotated by the radiologist and is magnified to be displayed more clearly in the bigger rectangles overlapping in the image.",
